t `invoke()` from `src/commands/Command.ts`.\n- Commands are discoverable through `src/utils/registry.ts` and exposed in `src/index.ts` command groups.\n- Existing shell implementation in `$ZC/helpers.zsh` uses `find ... -newermt` and copies files while optionally preserving directory structure.\n\n### Files to Reference\n\n| File | Purpose |\n| ---- | ------- |\n| `$ZC/helpers.zsh` | Source implementation of `syncDocs` behavior to port. |\n| `src/commands/Command.ts` | Base command abstraction and common helpers. |\n| `src/utils/registry.ts` | Command registration metadata and factory path. |\n| `src/index.ts` | CLI command wiring and execution flow. |\n\n### Technical Decisions\n\n- Destination root is fixed to `/home/delorenj/code/DeLoDocs/Projects`.\n- Repo name is determined by walking ancestors from CWD to nearest `.git`; fallback to current directory basename if no `.git` is found.\n- Keep shell-like behavior for options and copy semantics to minimize behavioral drift from current helper.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Tasks\n\nTo be defined in Step 3.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\nTo be defined in Step 3.\n\n## Additional Context\n\n### Dependencies\n\nNo external dependency additions expected.\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\nValidate with dry-run and real execution in repo and non-repo directories, including `--flat` and `--since` variants.\n\n### Notes\n\nUser preference confirms CLI shape should support `pjangler run COMMAND [options] [flags]` for implemented commands.\nEOF\npython - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-wip.md')\nprint('WROTE', p, 'exists=', p.exists(), 'bytes=', p.stat().st_size if p.exists() else 0)\nPY"} thread_id=019c1e07-020d-72a0-9ad2-56c1f9f62d0e
