O_NAME` resolution logic:\n  - start from current working directory\n  - walk upward to nearest directory containing `.git`\n  - use that directory basename as repo name\n  - if no `.git` ancestor exists, fallback to current directory basename\n- Option semantics remain unchanged from shell function:\n  - default `--since` window is `24 hours ago`\n  - optional `--flat` flag toggles flattening behavior\n  - source scan root remains `.`\n- Command should align with existing pjangler command architecture (class + registry + CLI wiring) rather than embedding ad-hoc script logic.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Tasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Add a runnable single-command execution path in CLI\n  - File: `src/index.ts`\n  - Action: Add `run <name>` command with options `-s, --since <time>`, `--flat`, `--dry-run`, `-f, --force`; wire execution by looking up command metadata and invoking the command class.\n  - Notes: Keep existing `init`, `list`, `recipe`, and `command` behavior unchanged.\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add command factory helpers in registry\n  - File: `src/utils/registry.ts`\n  - Action: Add helper(s) to create command instances by name from `COMMAND_REGISTRY` using `CommandContext`; keep type-safe return values and null handling.\n  - Notes: Reuse existing info access patterns (`getCommandInfo`, `getCommandNames`) and avoid duplicating mapping logic in CLI.\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement `SyncDocs` command class\n  - File: `src/commands/SyncDocs.ts`\n  - Action: Create class extending `Command` that encapsulates sync behavior and returns `InvokeResult`.\n  - Notes: Implement internal option payload (`since`, `flat`) and method(s) for repo detection, destination construction, file discovery, and copy behavior.\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement repo-name resolution with ancestor `.git` walk + fallback\n  - File: `src/commands/SyncDocs.ts`\n  - Action: Walk upward from `process.cwd()`; on nearest `.git` hit, use directory basename as repo name; if no hit, fallback to basename of `process.cwd()`.\n  - Notes: Treat both `.git` directory and `.git` file as valid repo markers.\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Implement destination and copy semantics matching shell behavior\n  - File: `src/commands/SyncDocs.ts`\n  - Action: Build destination `/home/delorenj/code/DeLoDocs/Projects/<repo>/docs/<YYYY-MM-DD>`; discover markdown files under `.` excluding `.git`; filter by mtime against parsed `since`; copy in flat or preserved-structure mode.\n  - Notes: In `dryRun`, report intended actions and count without writing files.\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Register `SyncDocs` in command registry\n  - File: `src/utils/registry.ts`\n  - Action: Import `SyncDocs` and add `COMMAND_REGISTRY` entry (name, description, group, class).\n  - Notes: Choose stable external command name for `run` path (e.g., `sync-docs`) and map to class.\n\n- [ ] Task 7: Update CLI help/usage output for runnable command path\n  - File: `src/index.ts`\n  - Action: Add clear examples in command/help output showing `pjangler run sync-docs --since \"24 hours ago\" --flat`.\n  - Notes: Keep compatibility with existing command-list/describe output.\n\n- [ ] Task 8: Validate behavior manually in repo and non-repo contexts\n  - File: `src/index.ts`, `src/commands/SyncDocs.ts`, `src/utils/registry.ts`\n  - Action: Run manual checks for default mode, `--flat`, custom `--since`, dry-run mode, and fallback repo-name behavior.\n  - Notes: Record verification outcomes in development notes or PR description.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC 1: Given I am in a git repository, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then files are copied to `/home/delorenj/code/DeLoDocs/Projects/<nearest-git-root-name>/docs/<today-YYYY-MM-DD>`.\n- [ ] AC 2: Given I am in nested subdirectories under a git repo, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then repo name comes from the nearest ancestor containing `.git` (repo root), not the current subdirectory.\n- [ ] AC 3: Given I am outside any git repo, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then destination uses the basename of the current directory as `<repo>`.\n- [ ] AC 4: Given I provide no `--since`, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then only markdown files modified since `24 hours ago` are considered.\n- [ ] AC 5: Given I pass `--since \"7 days ago\"`, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then filtering uses that window and ignores older markdown files.\n- [ ] AC 6: Given I do not pass `--flat`, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs`, then copied files preserve relative directory structure under destination.\n- [ ] AC 7: Given I pass `--flat`, when I run `pjangler run sync-docs --flat`, then copied files are placed directly in destination root.\n- [ ] AC 8: Given command is run with `--dry-run`, when sync executes, then no files or directories are created and output reports intended destination and file count.\n- [ ] AC 9: Given an unknown runnable command name, when I run `pjangler run <bad-name>`, then CLI exits with clear error and shows available command names.\n- [ ] AC 10: Given existing recipe and command-management commands, when I use them after this change, then their behavior remains unchanged.\n\n## Additional Context\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- No new third-party libraries are required.\n- Implementation depends on Node-compatible built-in modules (`fs`, `path`) and existing Commander usage.\n- Runtime dependency remains `commander` as already declared in `package.json`.\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n- Manual functional checks:\n  - In a git repo: run `pjangler run sync-docs` and verify repo-root-based destination path.\n  - In a nested repo folder: verify nearest `.git` ancestor naming.\n  - Outside repo: verify fallback to current directory basename.\n  - Run with `--flat` and verify flattened copy output.\n  - Run with custom `--since` and verify file inclusion window.\n  - Run with `--dry-run` and verify no filesystem writes.\n  - Run with invalid command name and verify error path.\n- Regression checks:\n  - `pjangler init <subsystem>` still works.